Introduction

Hibana, stylized as H!bana, was an independent South Korean live girl group managed by To Hermitage. They debuted on October 11, 2020 with the live performance of their self-titled single, "Hibana". They effectively disbanded on January 16, 2022 with the suspension of Nanako from the group due to contract violations. Their group name originates from Japanese and means "fire flower".
